HEDERA DEVELOPER GUIDE: Getting Started with Hedera
Category: Getting Started
Difficulty: Beginner
SDK Version: 2.50.0
Description: Complete guide to setting up your first Hedera application
Prerequisites: Basic programming knowledge, Node.js or Java
Estimated Time: 2-3 hours
Technologies: JavaScript/Java SDK, REST API
Code Language: JavaScript, Java
Hedera Services: HCS, HTS
Use Case: Basic account and token operations

HEDERA DEVELOPER GUIDE: Hedera Consensus Service Deep Dive
Category: Consensus Service
Difficulty: Advanced
SDK Version: 2.50.0
Description: Advanced guide to implementing consensus messaging with HCS
Prerequisites: Hedera basics, cryptography knowledge
Estimated Time: 4-6 hours
Technologies: Hedera SDK, Mirror Node API
Code Language: Java, Python
Hedera Services: HCS
Use Case: Audit trails, supply chain tracking

HEDERA DEVELOPER GUIDE: Smart Contracts 2.0 Development
Category: Smart Contracts
Difficulty: Intermediate
SDK Version: 2.50.0
Description: Building and deploying smart contracts on Hedera
Prerequisites: Solidity, Ethereum development experience
Estimated Time: 3-5 hours
Technologies: Solidity, Hardhat, Hedera SDK
Code Language: Solidity, JavaScript
Hedera Services: Smart Contracts 2.0, HTS
Use Case: DeFi applications, NFT marketplaces

HEDERA DEVELOPER GUIDE: Token Service Integration Guide
Category: Token Service
Difficulty: Intermediate
SDK Version: 2.50.0
Description: Creating and managing fungible and non-fungible tokens
Prerequisites: Hedera basics, token economics
Estimated Time: 2-4 hours
Technologies: Hedera SDK, REST API
Code Language: JavaScript, Go
Hedera Services: HTS
Use Case: Token creation, NFT minting

HEDERA DEVELOPER GUIDE: File Service for Data Storage
Category: File Service
Difficulty: Beginner
SDK Version: 2.50.0
Description: Storing and retrieving files on the Hedera network
Prerequisites: Basic Hedera knowledge
Estimated Time: 1-2 hours
Technologies: Hedera SDK
Code Language: Python, Java
Hedera Services: HFS
Use Case: Document storage, data immutability
